Immediately use the 'vial' tool on this combined solid item; this consistently produces an extract with a value of 60, regardless of whether the initial solids were mundane or magical. The 'vial' tool used on single solid ingredients also gives a value of 30. Avoid using the 'vial' tool on liquid or gas ingredients, as it often results in negative values or 'botched extraction'. The 'filter' tool consistently decreases item value and adds negative features, so it's best to avoid it. Also, combining valuable extracts seems to reduce their overall value. Aim for a value of 60 and submit.

message: The key to high scores is transforming ingredients into liquid extracts and then combining them strategically. Always use the 'vial' tool on solid ingredients first to create valuable liquid extracts (e.g., solid -> liquid extract value 30). Avoid combining solids and liquids directly, as it results in very negative values. For the highest value, combine a mundane liquid extract with a magical liquid extract (e.g., 'rose petal extract' + 'sunstone extract' yielded 100 value). The 'filter' tool can sometimes increase value but can also introduce 'botched filtering' or decrease value, so use it cautiously. Combining more than two items (especially three or more liquids) often leads to 'overcomplicated' items with significantly reduced value. Focus on quality two-item liquid combinations.

message: Directly combining ingredients usually results in negative values. The most successful path I found was combining a magical solid with a mundane liquid, then using the 'vial' tool on the resulting item. This yielded a positive value, even with 'failed extraction' features. The 'filter' tool consistently led to 'botched filtering' and often decreased value, so I would advise caution when using it. Focus on identifying specific ingredient types that interact well with tools.
